body: Μῦς, mouse, Mus musculus. The Egyptian kind is probably Hierax, those said to walk on two feet are the Jerboa. The Pontic kind said to ruminate. Mus Citillus, _Schneider_, 5, 50; reproduction, 178; Persian, Egyptian, and many other kinds, _ib._; manner of drinking, 205; white mice in Pontus, 216; Arabian mice, 226; Lybian, _ib._; the Pontic mouse is said to ruminate, 278.
